Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
high-speed \high-speed\ adj. 1. same as {fast}; as, fast film. Opposite of {slow}. [WordNet 1.5]
2. performed at a high rate of speed; as, a high-speed auto chase on the freeway.
Syn: hot. [WordNet 1.5]
high-speed adj 1: operating at high speed; "a high-speed food processor"; "a high-velocity shell" [syn: {high-velocity}] 2: taking place at high speed; "a high-speed chase"
